file_content.text: Help! Boss! Help! Come back! She too tough!
Help! Boss! Help! Come back! He too tough!
I heard Vause was a holy terror, why'd he leave you to do the dirty work?
Is your boss a coward?
Quit squealing, you're making me queasy.
Get a grip, would you?
Just you and me now, pig.
Vause left you to die.
Don't kill. Don't kill! I give up! I not worth money!
Cooperate and you might live.
I want to know where your boss is headed.
Talk and you might live.
Give up Vause and I'll let you walk.
I don't want you.
Please don't kill! I can't help! I know nothing!
Spill your guts before I do.
Talk! [Hit Muglund]
I sorry I attack you! I sorry! I don't want to!
Captain think we weak, make him look bad, take us on hunt to show how we be strong. We hunt small prey, he hunt big.
You come and Captain say you small, so we fight, but you not small! I just want to go back to mop decks!
Waste someone else's time.
Get lost.
I not bother you again! Thank you!
All right, go on. You ever see me again, run.
Okay, okay, you can go.
I never see you again. If I do I look other way! Thank you!
From the sound of things, I think we're doing the White Maw a favor by getting rid of Vause.
Fry piggy.
Useless. [Kill Muglund]
Finally, my ears were starting to ring.
Hmph, Vause didn't think much of us.
Ugh, they smell even worse with blaster burns.
Come on, we're paying Blizz another visit.
See what he thinks when I'm wearing him as boots.
I'll teach him the hard way.
I can trail him. Come on.
Hadn't taken Vause for a blowhard.
Can't believe he ran off.
Don't think he is. Just picky.
Point the way, Torian.
Keep on him.
Right.
